HEADWORD: hypernymy
<hw>hypernymy</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the relation of being
superordinate or belonging to a higher (more abstract) rank or class.
Inverse of <inv>hyponymy</inv>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> superordination.</syn>⟦br⟧
